The exhibits show year of technology introduction (Initial) and final values in year 2030.
Timing of technology maturity varies due to the complexity of the technologies and is determined by OTT Program Manager input as well as goals set forth by the offices.
Changes in attributes can be assumed to occur non-linearly during the analysis period; e.g. significant improvements may occur shortly after introduction with lesser changes occurring in later years.
In some cases, the technology may be assumed to be commercially mature from the time when it is introduced into the vehicle class.
Years of introduction vary among the car and truck size classes to account for market growth and development.
As Exhibits 2-2 through 2-6 indicate, in some cases, technology characteristics also vary among the size classes both for conventional gasoline and alternative technologies.
