Technologies considered in QM 2002 include natural gas engines, advanced diesel engines that are highly efficient and emit low levels of pollution in all classes and market segments, and hybrid drive trains in the medium class.
The incremental vehicle costs and fuel economy ratios of the advanced heavy vehicle technologies are indicated in Exhibit 3-26.
The table implicitly indicates the assumption that as a new technology is introduced into the market place and sales shares increase, costs are reduced.
