Exhibit 3-27 illustrates market penetration forecasts for heavy vehicles.
For the assumptions utilized, the natural gas truck characteristics are not economically competitive except in the year 2000 in Class 7 and 8 trucks.
Advanced diesel technology has the best penetration in Type 3 trucks, which also have the greatest utilization level in terms of miles driven per year.
Penetration in Type 2 trucks is also significant.
